Drawable
public class Missile
extends GameElement

Logic representation for a missile.

A missile is represented by a line which begins at a certain point and then it expands until it reaches a goal point or explodes.

Author:
Luis Carlos Mateos

public Missile(int ix,
               int iy,
               int gx,
               int gy,
               double speed)
Constructor of the Missile class.

It initializes all the parameters of the missile and calculates a template needed by the guidance missile guidance system. The movement of the missile follows the Pythagorean Theorem.

Parameters:
ix - origin x coordinate
iy - origin y coordinate
gx - destination x coordinate
gy - destination x coordinate
speed - speed

Method Detail

move

public boolean move()
Calculates the movement of a missile and checks whether it has reached its destination

Since we have calculated the delta coordinates, we only need to add the delta value to the current point to know where exactly is the next point.

It is important to note that this model assumes that the Canvas top-left coordinate is (0,Y_MAX) and its bottom-right coordinate is (X_MAX,0)

Returns:
true if the missile could advance to a further point.
